│ when widening i32 to i64 in VPScalarIVStepsRecipe::execute on targets where   │
│ BaseIVTy is 64-bit FP but index types are 32-bit. Using CreateZExtOrTrunc     │
│ fixes the type adjustment, preventing the invalid constantexpr cast and       │
│ allowing the loop-vectorizer to proceed. This change is safe, consistent with │
│ index semantics, and aligns with existing code patterns in vector pointer/end │
│ pointer recipes."})                                                           │
